---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="ToolCraft terms of use — guidelines for using our free online tools."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
        <span>Terms of Use</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-content">
      <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By using ToolCraft ("the Site"), you agree to these Terms of Use. If you do not 
        agree, please do not use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Use of Tools</h2>
      <p>
        All tools are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. You use them at 
        your own risk. We make no guarantees about the accuracy or reliability of tool outputs.
      </p>

      <h2>No Upload Storage</h2>
      <p>
        Files processed through browser-based tools are not stored on our servers. 
        They are processed locally in your browser and are not accessible to us.
      </p>

      <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        The ToolCraft name, logo, and site design are our intellectual property. 
        Tool outputs are yours to use as you see fit.
      </p>

      <h2>Premium Services</h2>
      <p>
        Some tools offer premium tiers. Payments are processed through third-party 
        payment processors. Refund policies are determined at the point of sale.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        ToolCraft shall not be liable for any damages arising from the use or inability 
        to use our tools or services.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes are effective 
        immediately upon posting.
      </p>

      <p><em>Last updated: December 2025</em></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
